            {
                "comment": "Aris is one of the best professors that I've ever had. He's ambitious in his programming and truly believes in the arts and it's importance in everyday life. He goes above and beyond to help his driven students in their professional careers while also encouraging interest in others. He has a gift for teaching and inspiring those around him.",
                "difficulty_rating": 3,
                "quality_rating": 5
            },
            {
                "comment": "One of the appreciated profs at this University. He has the knowledge and should be respected. Although I made bad projects, he encouraged me well.",
                "difficulty_rating": 1,
                "quality_rating": 5
            },
            {
                "comment": "Aris is a tough critic which is what I look for in a professor. He tells it to you straight but in hopes of helping you grow. His material knowledge is unparalleled but he also has a good sense of political awareness. I love that he is responsive to emails and generally helpful outside of class/studio time. Also a wonderful and successful artist",
                "difficulty_rating": 3,
                "quality_rating": 4
            },
            {
                "comment": "Aris is by far the most amazing professor I have had as an undergraduate (this is my fourth year). Unlike many art teachers, he doesn't think he's better than everyone and wants everyone to succeed not only in his class, but in the real world. He tries to give his students connections to other artists and overall is an amazing amazing person!",
                "difficulty_rating": 2,
                "quality_rating": 5
            },
            {
                "comment": "Aris is very knowledgeable, interesting, and fair.  We had a small class, and he let our interests drive the curriculum.  I learned a lot and will take another course with Aris.",
